result.name: Saam Hui Yaat

reviews.text: I came to this place on a recommendation from a youtube video. Yes its tasty and affordable compared to the ones in the other areas. I'll skip the chee cheong fun.

Friendly service & good value dim sum! English menu available also with all the usual dim sum classics. Come for an insight into the ritual of authentic HK dim sum. Open super early for all you jet lagged travellers! They'll ask you what tea you would like when you sit down & give you a bowl to wash your cutlery and bowls.

Lo Mai Gai (Glutinous Rice with Chicken) was excellent as was the Siu Mai & Har Gao.

Least stressful place to eat! A small dim sum eatery but it represents the best Hong Kong can offer... Fantastic food, low price, English menu and most importantly, very friendly staff... The man serving us even helped us with the washing of the utensils and pouring of the tea! What a place... Best kept secret of HK!
Very authentic and pleasant atmosphere. Tasty food!
The last few dim sum tea house in HK with local hand made dim sum, which is not by machine nor from China. Some rumors say it will be closed soon after the chef retired. Go while it still exist.

result.name: 叁去壹點心粉麵飯

reviews.text: 坐位不舒適但食物味道很好😋很受街坊歡迎而且他們在新假期週刊及一啲旅遊雜誌都有上榜

第一次來
12點去客人挺多 八成都是老街坊 
點了鳳爪 味道不錯 但是最後看到一隻蒼蠅埋在最下層😂阿彌陀佛🙏
蒸粉粿 我不喜歡
叉燒腸粉 皮太厚
窩蛋牛肉飯 好吃 有淡淡陳皮香味
加上茶水 一共87港幣
來這裡 吃的是懷舊氣氛。食物普普
懷舊茶居已有60多年了！點心是自家製作不是內地貨色，厨房師傅手勢了得夠鑊氣，我已光顧了近30年‼
食咗隻蝦餃先記得影相，古早味，但唔係蓮香果種，係舊樓街坊茶居。食物一般，星洲炒米唔得。聽講老闆想退休，結業在即。
幾張桌子，十多位常客，在此地据守相信超過四十年，喜懷舊，食傳统的你要到，老店賣小見小了！
